        "subject": "LU-3390 iokit: Interop failure in mds-survey, stripe_count=1",
        "message": "LU-3390 iokit: Interop failure in mds-survey, stripe_count=1\n\nThe information returned from \"lctl device_list\" changed between\nb2_3 and b2_4 causing interop failures.\n\nIn b2_3, \"lctl device_list\" on the MDS returns lines containing\n\"... UP osc lscratch-OST0000-osc-MDT0000 ...\" for each OST.\nIn b2_4, the OST information looks like\n\"... UP osp lscratch-OST0000-osc-MDT0000 ...\".\n\nA patch for LU-1303 (http://review.whamcloud.com/4087) fixes this\nby modifying mds-survey to look for and parse lines with \"osc\" or\n\"osp\". We adopt this fix here for b2_3.\n\nThis is a \"fortestonly\" patch to show that this fixes the interop\nerror of sanity test 225b failing.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=sanity serverdistro=el6 serverarch=x86_64 serverjob=lustre-master serverbuild=0\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2b767c0a62cd9c5523189e11f2df3b8bc3a08439\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_3"
    }
  },
